WEBVTT

00:29.200 --> 00:31.560
48.

00:37.840 --> 00:40.600
AUDIENCE GROANS

00:45.600 --> 00:48.240
MUSIC: Black Dog by Led Zeppelin

01:07.600 --> 01:09.680
You call it the luck of the Irish.

01:18.840 --> 01:22.599
I'm exactly what the game needs.
I'm an entertainer.

01:22.600 --> 01:25.319
I'm always conscious of the man
in the street who pays a fiver,

01:25.320 --> 01:28.479
and that man wants to see fast play.

01:28.480 --> 01:30.839
If I can help someone escape that dreary,

01:30.840 --> 01:35.399
working-class environment, then
that's not a bad thing, is it?

01:35.400 --> 01:39.720
You just get my name right in the
papers, it's Alexander the Great.

01:41.480 --> 01:44.879
I thought we agreed on Hurricane.
Hurricane Higgins.

01:44.880 --> 01:46.320
THEY CHEER

01:56.440 --> 01:58.759
Just there, on the left.

01:58.760 --> 02:02.919
Ladies and gentlemen, please
welcome to the Pot Black studio,

02:02.920 --> 02:07.560
the 1972 world snooker champion,
Alex "Hurricane" Higgins.

02:17.160 --> 02:22.439
Excuse me, Mr Higgins. Mr Higgins!
It's just we do have a dress code.

02:22.440 --> 02:24.479
I know you do, Ted, and
I'd love to wear that,

02:24.480 --> 02:26.879
but I can't do the tie on
account of my neck disease.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.519
You do know I have a
neck disease, don't you?

02:29.520 --> 02:33.679
It's the same one that afflicts the
violinists. I have a doctor's note.

02:33.680 --> 02:35.800
Come on in, you can read it for yourself.

02:41.400 --> 02:46.279
Mr Higgins, I must ask you
not to urinate in the sink.

02:46.280 --> 02:48.320
GIGGLING

02:49.840 --> 02:54.240
Forgive me, Ted. I'd introduce
you, but I don't know their names.

02:55.880 --> 02:59.999
Two girls, straight off the streets
of Birmingham. He's banned.

03:00.000 --> 03:02.719
GIGGLING

03:02.720 --> 03:06.840
MUSIC: Liquidator by Harry J Allstars

03:27.200 --> 03:28.720
Excuse me.

03:31.360 --> 03:32.680
Excuse me.

03:34.320 --> 03:36.599
I was wondering if you
might provide me with some

03:36.600 --> 03:40.760
information about the tables and the
facilities in this establishment.

03:44.160 --> 03:48.279
You know, what the, er,
pockets are like and the, er,

03:48.280 --> 03:50.040
and the... the slate.

03:53.080 --> 03:55.680
Do you need me to call your mum?

03:57.360 --> 03:58.840
And what about the mat?

04:01.760 --> 04:04.080
MUSIC: Jeepster by T. Rex

04:05.160 --> 04:07.200
How are you?

04:09.280 --> 04:13.839
- Hi, Alex.
- Hi, how are you? You look beautiful.
- Thank you.

04:13.840 --> 04:15.919
Thank you.

04:15.920 --> 04:17.800
Hi, Alex.

04:27.560 --> 04:29.160
GIGGLING

04:48.960 --> 04:51.559
Alex Higgins.

04:51.560 --> 04:53.480
Hurricane Higgins?

04:56.240 --> 04:57.360
The snooker player?

04:58.600 --> 05:00.200
What's snooker?

05:02.880 --> 05:04.240
Excuse me.

05:07.800 --> 05:10.360
Please, what's your name?

05:13.120 --> 05:17.360
HE HUMS "LET'S FACE THE MUSIC AND DANCE"

05:25.000 --> 05:27.560
DOOR OPENS

05:34.920 --> 05:39.959
- What are you doing?
- I don't know, he's been at it about an hour.

05:39.960 --> 05:41.480
- Is this the lad?
- Yeah.

05:42.840 --> 05:44.719
God, he's pale, isn't he?

05:44.720 --> 05:48.119
I bet he gets sunburnt
when he opens the fridge.

05:48.120 --> 05:49.799
He's thin and all.

05:49.800 --> 05:52.320
I've seen more meat on
Linda McCartney's fork.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.679
He doesn't say much, does he?

05:57.680 --> 06:00.319
He's like Marcel Marceau in a library.

06:00.320 --> 06:03.320
Parlez-vous the English, senorita?

06:06.040 --> 06:09.639
Sorry, Mr Hearn. I did find
your jokes very funny,

06:09.640 --> 06:13.199
but I like to concentrate
when I'm practising.

06:13.200 --> 06:17.199
- Do you want a drink, Davis? It is Steve Davis, isn't it?
- Yes.

06:17.200 --> 06:19.679
Yes, it is, Mr Hearn. That's very kind.
Milk, please.

06:19.680 --> 06:22.520
- Cold milk is fine.
- What, you don't drink?

06:24.040 --> 06:25.479
I like an eggnog.

06:25.480 --> 06:27.520
You know, at Christmas and...

06:29.000 --> 06:30.839
No, actually, I don't like it.

06:30.840 --> 06:33.639
What do you do, then? Apart from snooker?

06:33.640 --> 06:38.039
Smoke? Gamble? Drugs? Girls?

06:38.040 --> 06:41.199
Boys? Inflatable dolls?

06:41.200 --> 06:45.159
- I play mental chess.
- Is he any good?

06:45.160 --> 06:47.639
I don't know, boss, I
can't play mental chess.

06:47.640 --> 06:51.799
- No, at snooker, you wally!
- Oh, yeah.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.640
He'll beat anyone who walks in that door.

06:56.160 --> 06:57.960
PLANE FLIES OVERHEAD

06:59.480 --> 07:00.999
Lynn!

07:01.000 --> 07:02.799
Lynn!

07:02.800 --> 07:04.759
Lynn.

07:04.760 --> 07:07.559
- I tried phoning.
- I know. 20 times.

07:07.560 --> 07:11.160
I'm not great with the phone. I
thought I'd charm you in person.

07:12.640 --> 07:15.039
Look, I'm sorry about the other night.

07:15.040 --> 07:16.679
I'm not really like that.

07:16.680 --> 07:19.959
Really? That's not what I've heard.

07:19.960 --> 07:24.159
I'm sometimes like that, but I
can tell you deserve better.

07:24.160 --> 07:26.439
Let me take you out.

07:26.440 --> 07:28.360
What's the worst that can happen?

07:39.200 --> 07:43.359
Now, the trick is, keep
the bottom one still

07:43.360 --> 07:46.399
and get the top one to
pinch the food together.

07:46.400 --> 07:47.640
Like this.

07:55.040 --> 07:56.999
I don't think these are proper chopsticks.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.000
SHE GIGGLES

08:02.560 --> 08:05.959
That's me. Winning my first tournament.

08:05.960 --> 08:07.279
I know.

08:07.280 --> 08:09.160
I haven't changed a bit.

08:12.560 --> 08:16.479
- Sandy? That's a girl's name.
- That's what my big sisters call me.

08:16.480 --> 08:21.039
- They look like they can keep you out of trouble.
- I wish.

08:21.040 --> 08:23.519
- No, I'm always on the road.
- Don't tell me.

08:23.520 --> 08:27.080
- Hurricane Higgins gets lonely.
- It's not all razzmatazz, Lynn.

08:28.560 --> 08:31.479
I can be playing in front of 1,000 people,

08:31.480 --> 08:34.119
all the people at home
watching on the telly.

08:34.120 --> 08:35.679
But I'm a snooker player.

08:35.679 --> 08:37.799
In the end, you're always on your own.

08:40.960 --> 08:42.958
Me mates were right.

08:42.960 --> 08:45.760
Hurricane Higgins is a right flash bastard.

08:49.600 --> 08:51.720
But I like Alex Higgins.

08:55.360 --> 08:56.559
Come on.

08:56.560 --> 08:58.720
Where are we going?

08:59.760 --> 09:04.960
MUSIC: Hit Me With Your Rhythm Stick
by Ian Dury and the Blockheads

09:28.160 --> 09:30.039
Here he is - the man of the moment.

09:30.040 --> 09:31.559
The Hurricane in Romford!

09:31.560 --> 09:33.039
Get this man a drink.

09:33.040 --> 09:35.959
- Thanks for coming down, Alex, I really appreciate it.
- Pint of lager.

09:35.960 --> 09:38.319
It'll do wonders for the kid.
He's good, but he's green,

09:38.320 --> 09:40.479
especially in front of top
players like yourself.

09:40.480 --> 09:42.199
Baz, it'll be difficult for me

09:42.200 --> 09:44.119
to play snooker with
your head up my jacksie.

09:44.120 --> 09:45.999
Noted. Noted.

09:46.000 --> 09:48.599
Here he is. Davis!

09:48.600 --> 09:49.640
Davis!

10:01.880 --> 10:04.200
Come on, Steve!

10:20.800 --> 10:25.080
What happened? Did a carrot fuck a snail...
up the arse?

10:35.120 --> 10:37.440
- Yes!
- Go on!

10:43.280 --> 10:44.680
- Yes!
- Yes!

10:46.640 --> 10:50.199
You know, Baz, I'm sorry, but
I can't keep my eyes open.

10:50.200 --> 10:54.959
What do you say we make this interesting?

10:54.960 --> 10:56.720
If you say so, Alex.

11:06.520 --> 11:08.920
Looks like I've found my
game but lost my hearing.

11:10.880 --> 11:12.519
Sorry, Barry, that's a lot of money.

11:12.520 --> 11:15.120
Don't you worry, you're
not going to lose. OK?

11:16.960 --> 11:18.679
Yes!

11:18.680 --> 11:20.759
Go on, my son. Come on.

11:20.760 --> 11:22.439
Come on!

11:22.440 --> 11:24.400
STEVE POTS BALL

11:25.800 --> 11:27.880
STEVE POTS BALL

11:39.880 --> 11:41.679
Yes!

11:41.680 --> 11:43.560
CHEERING

11:49.360 --> 11:52.679
What did I tell ya? I said
he'd do it, didn't I?

11:52.680 --> 11:54.160
You owe me 40.

11:56.240 --> 11:57.919
Cheers.

11:57.920 --> 12:00.919
Well done. We'll have a
drink later to celebrate.

12:00.920 --> 12:02.719
So, what do you think of the lad?

12:02.720 --> 12:05.439
I don't. I'd have killed
him in a proper match.

12:05.440 --> 12:07.919
Without this bunch of hooligans, I mean.

12:07.920 --> 12:10.479
This place is a fucking disgrace.

12:10.480 --> 12:15.039
That top cushion has got more
bounce than a pair of Page 3 tits.

12:15.040 --> 12:17.080
Thanks for coming, Alex.

12:19.960 --> 12:22.199
Get that man a pint!

12:22.200 --> 12:24.719
Of milk! And make it gold top!

12:24.720 --> 12:26.719
LAUGHTER

12:26.720 --> 12:29.319
Taxi for the Hurricane!

12:29.320 --> 12:31.080
CHEERING

12:35.400 --> 12:38.679
I've been waiting a long time
to meet a man like you, Davis.

12:38.680 --> 12:41.639
I bet that's something you
don't hear very often.

12:41.640 --> 12:43.319
HE CHUCKLES

12:43.320 --> 12:47.919
You see, I think snooker is
going to be big. Properly big.

12:47.920 --> 12:50.079
Bigger even than wrestling.

12:50.080 --> 12:52.719
I'm being serious.

12:52.720 --> 12:54.999
And I want us to go into
partnership together.

12:55.000 --> 12:58.079
We can be like Giant
Haystacks and Big Daddy.

12:58.080 --> 13:02.239
Do you mean, like, what, 50/50?

13:02.240 --> 13:05.719
Jesus, Davis! I was only going to take ten.

13:05.720 --> 13:08.199
I think you'd better let me
do the haggling from now on.

13:08.200 --> 13:12.759
Look, you just pot the balls, and
I'll take care of everything else.

13:12.760 --> 13:14.759
Everything what else?

13:14.760 --> 13:17.439
I'm going to make you - and me -

13:17.440 --> 13:19.800
very, very rich.

13:20.840 --> 13:22.080
How's that sound?

13:27.560 --> 13:31.199
Jesus, Davis, it's like
strangling a lettuce.

13:31.200 --> 13:33.040
Come here, you big nugget.

13:34.200 --> 13:36.000
I hope that's your snooker cue.

13:38.280 --> 13:39.840
Ha-ha-ha!

13:40.840 --> 13:43.759
That's it! That's what the
grannies like to see.

13:43.760 --> 13:47.399
A nice, clean-cut,
well-dressed young man...

13:47.400 --> 13:49.319
- bending over a table.
- Barry...

13:49.320 --> 13:53.759
Come on, princess, give us a twirl,
show us what you got back there.

13:53.760 --> 13:55.799
No. Something's not right.

13:55.800 --> 13:59.159
Spiros. Can you try him in a
different pair of socks, please?

13:59.160 --> 14:02.119
- COMMENTATOR: - 'It's about nine
o'clock, people have been queuing

14:02.120 --> 14:04.879
'outside, and the queue was
stretching way down the street,

14:04.880 --> 14:07.359
'and it's a very busy scene
inside the Crucible.

14:07.360 --> 14:10.399
'And it's that, I think, because
all the nine players, who are left

14:10.400 --> 14:12.919
'in this championship, are
all playing matches today,

14:12.920 --> 14:14.279
'and this is very important.

14:14.280 --> 14:15.679
'Let's take a look at the line-up

14:15.680 --> 14:18.239
'of the championship as
it stands at the moment.'

14:18.240 --> 14:21.999
Jesus, Bill, did you not get
those Jane Fonda videos I sent?

14:22.000 --> 14:25.959
- Kiss my ass.
- Come on, I'll introduce you.

14:25.960 --> 14:30.079
Kirk Stevens, lock up your daughters.

14:30.080 --> 14:33.080
Tony Knowles, lock up your wife.

14:34.160 --> 14:38.119
Oh, Cliff Thorburn, lock up your mam.

14:38.120 --> 14:40.719
And Dennis Taylor, lock up your granny!

14:40.720 --> 14:46.159
This is Jimmy White - the
whirlwind amateur world champion,

14:46.160 --> 14:50.319
who, one day, when I've retired,
will be the Embassy World Champion.

14:50.320 --> 14:51.559
What have you got a cigar for?

14:51.560 --> 14:53.519
He doesn't look old
enough to buy cigarettes!

14:53.520 --> 14:56.600
- I've just become a dad.
- Yeah!

14:58.480 --> 15:00.159
Jesus!

15:00.160 --> 15:03.079
What did Barry do to you?

15:03.080 --> 15:05.319
You look like... an undertaker.

15:05.320 --> 15:07.279
No, you don't.

15:07.280 --> 15:08.919
He looks like the cadaver.

15:08.920 --> 15:10.999
LAUGHTER

15:11.000 --> 15:14.439
I was told that they had...
asteroids in here.

15:14.440 --> 15:15.959
Asteroids?

15:15.960 --> 15:19.279
Isn't that what you had, Dennis?
Didn't they give you a cream for it?

15:19.280 --> 15:21.640
LAUGHTER

15:23.040 --> 15:25.159
I'll have a pint. Jimmy, what do you want?

15:25.160 --> 15:27.159
Er, lager, please.

15:27.160 --> 15:30.119
- COMMENTATOR:
- 'Alex Higgins, '72 champion,

15:30.120 --> 15:33.680
'against Steve Davis, the new
sensation of the snooker world.

15:39.720 --> 15:43.119
'From Belfast, the quickest
potter on the planet,

15:43.120 --> 15:47.159
'please welcome to the Crucible,
Alex "Hurricane" Higgins.'

15:47.160 --> 15:49.360
We're not in Romford now.

15:52.720 --> 15:54.360
CHEERING

16:03.080 --> 16:05.999
'For his first appearance in a
world championship quarterfinal,

16:06.000 --> 16:09.439
'from London, please welcome Steve Davis.'

16:09.440 --> 16:11.120
Go on, my son.

16:14.120 --> 16:16.080
APPLAUSE

16:22.640 --> 16:25.319
- COMMENTATOR:
- 'Well, Steve Davis had a go there.

16:25.320 --> 16:28.280
'And I'm afraid it's going
to be very costly for him.'

16:38.920 --> 16:40.760
CHEERING

16:46.160 --> 16:48.440
'That slight upset has upset Steve.'

16:53.720 --> 16:55.960
CHEERING

16:58.520 --> 17:02.159
MUSIC: Mr Blue Sky by ELO

17:02.160 --> 17:03.760
Come on!

17:06.040 --> 17:09.160
- COMMENTATORS:
- 'A terrific performance by Alex Higgins.

17:14.960 --> 17:17.799
'Arrogant and box-office
snooker by Alex Higgins.

17:17.800 --> 17:19.559
'Absolutely brilliant.'

17:19.560 --> 17:21.519
'Alex is such a talented player.

17:21.520 --> 17:23.799
'There stands the world trophy.

17:23.800 --> 17:26.599
'That, together with £15,000.'

17:32.680 --> 17:34.600
Good luck.

17:38.480 --> 17:40.159
May the best man win.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.879
Awful gracious of you, Grinder,

17:41.880 --> 17:44.239
but at least let's go through the motions.

17:44.240 --> 17:47.919
'So please put your hands
together for Cliff Thorburn!

17:47.920 --> 17:50.439
'And looking to win his second world crown,

17:50.440 --> 17:55.960
'from Northern Ireland, please
welcome Alex "Hurricane" Higgins!'

18:03.480 --> 18:05.399
'So Alex goes into the lead.

18:05.400 --> 18:10.039
'In a very favourable position indeed.

18:10.040 --> 18:11.599
POTS BALL

18:11.600 --> 18:14.560
'Beautifully controlled.

18:17.320 --> 18:19.079
'That's a beautiful shot.'

18:19.080 --> 18:21.159
That's kamikaze snooker!

18:21.160 --> 18:22.640
I know.

18:23.800 --> 18:24.960
Magic, innit?

18:28.400 --> 18:31.079
- AUDIENCE: Ooh!
- 'That was a leap of the ball...'

18:31.080 --> 18:32.319
What'd he take that on for?

18:32.320 --> 18:34.639
What does he think this is?
Mission: Impossible?

18:34.640 --> 18:36.399
♪ Boom-boom boom-boom... ♪

18:36.400 --> 18:41.079
"This snooker player will
self-destruct in five minutes."

18:41.080 --> 18:43.999
'And Alex watching every stroke.

18:44.000 --> 18:48.960
'Surely seeing the world
title run away from him.'

18:52.520 --> 18:53.880
< POTS BALL

18:57.080 --> 18:58.719
Come on, Cliff!

18:58.720 --> 19:03.079
'He just wants this frame to
become World Snooker Champion.

19:03.080 --> 19:06.599
'And that shot must truly
sadden the heart... '

19:06.600 --> 19:08.480
Alex!

19:11.720 --> 19:13.639
He blew it!

19:13.640 --> 19:17.439
Playing to the gallery like there's
an audience award for the best shot.

19:17.440 --> 19:20.359
You can't take a round
of applause to the bank.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.559
He's like a little boy lost.

19:22.560 --> 19:27.559
He's desperate for approval. Emotion,
Davis, is the enemy of success.

19:27.560 --> 19:29.919
- OK, boss.
- Good.

19:29.920 --> 19:31.440
But we can do better.

19:33.400 --> 19:38.239
We need to create an aura of
invincibility around you.

19:38.240 --> 19:40.359
Right, bear with me, Davis.

19:40.360 --> 19:42.039
I want you to sit up on that seat

19:42.040 --> 19:44.599
like you're on a khazi,
doing your business.

19:44.600 --> 19:46.120
Come on!

19:51.440 --> 19:55.239
That's how you should sit when
you're in tournaments, right?

19:55.240 --> 19:57.279
Cross your legs a little bit.

19:57.280 --> 19:59.359
- What, have I finished on the khazi now?
- Yeah.

19:59.360 --> 20:03.359
Yeah. Look, you're there, all right?

20:03.360 --> 20:05.199
You're at the Crucible.

20:05.200 --> 20:06.719
Yeah?

20:06.720 --> 20:08.119
Picture it.

20:08.120 --> 20:10.799
Last frame. OK?

20:10.800 --> 20:13.399
Everybody's waiting for
you to make the shot.

20:13.400 --> 20:15.999
OK? You're thinking it
through, thinking it through.

20:16.000 --> 20:17.879
Open your eyes.

20:17.880 --> 20:21.159
I want you to feel like
you've seen a lot of trauma.

20:21.160 --> 20:24.359
But I don't want to see your
thoughts, I want to see nothing.

20:24.360 --> 20:26.999
Just eyes. Dead.

20:27.000 --> 20:28.880
That's my boy. Good.

20:31.640 --> 20:32.680
OK.

20:40.680 --> 20:43.720
You need something else. You need a drink.

20:48.600 --> 20:49.839
No. No, no, no, no.

20:49.840 --> 20:53.759
Look, it's not a cup of
warm milk before bedtime.

20:53.760 --> 20:55.399
It's a weapon.

20:55.400 --> 20:57.679
No, no, no. Don't gulp it.

20:57.680 --> 20:59.160
Just... just sip it.

21:00.440 --> 21:03.079
Don't sip it either.

21:03.080 --> 21:05.160
- What else is there?
- OK.

21:10.360 --> 21:12.279
Just pick it up.

21:12.280 --> 21:15.080
Put it to your lips and then
put it back down again.

21:21.400 --> 21:23.080
- Why?
- I don't know.

21:24.080 --> 21:25.520
But it's terrifying.

21:26.840 --> 21:29.879
Er... won't the other players
just think I'm a wally?

21:29.880 --> 21:32.199
No, Davis, they won't.

21:32.200 --> 21:35.439
They'll think you're a total arsehole.

21:35.440 --> 21:38.519
And that... is what we want.

21:38.520 --> 21:41.080
Think of it as... mental snooker.

21:54.680 --> 21:57.720
< MUFFLED SPEECH

22:00.880 --> 22:02.839
- SLURRED:
- No, it was luck, Thorburn,

22:02.840 --> 22:05.599
that's what it was. You got lucky today.

22:05.600 --> 22:08.639
That referee's always hated me.
They all hate me.

22:08.640 --> 22:09.959
- You fucking cheat!
- 'Alex...'

22:09.960 --> 22:12.279
Don't you FUCKING hang up on me!

22:12.280 --> 22:15.159
Alex, what are you doing? Alex, stop it!

22:15.160 --> 22:16.239
Alex!

22:16.240 --> 22:17.839
Alex, listen to me!

22:17.840 --> 22:20.879
Listen, it's all right!

22:20.880 --> 22:22.439
Alex!

22:22.440 --> 22:23.960
It's all right.

22:25.000 --> 22:26.919
Alex, listen to me, listen.

22:26.920 --> 22:29.999
Listen, there's always next year, OK?

22:30.000 --> 22:31.799
It's all right.

22:31.800 --> 22:34.199
MUSIC: Another One Bites The Dust by Queen

22:34.200 --> 22:40.679
'Steve Davis, making his debut
in a big-time championship...

